    {
      "parameters": {
        "toolDescription": "Call this tool to take action in the Contact database.",
        "text": "={{ /*n8n-auto-generated-fromAI-override*/ $fromAI('Prompt__User_Message_', ``, 'string') }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=### Overview\nYou are a contact manager with access to a Google Sheets contact database. Your job is to look up or save contact information accurately.\n\n### Tools\n- **get Contact** — Search the contact database by name or email. Use this to retrieve a contact's email address or phone number.\n- **add or update Contact** — Add a new contact or update an existing one.\n\n### Rules\n- When asked for a contact's email, always use the **get Contact** tool — never guess or fabricate an email address.\n- Return the exact email address found in the database. If no contact is found, clearly say \"No contact found for [Name]\" so the Master Agent can inform the user.\n- When returning results, always include both the name AND the email in your response so the calling agent can use it directly.\n\n### Response Format\nAlways respond in this format when a contact is found:\n\"Found contact: [Name] — Email: [email@example.com]\"\n\nIf not found:\n\"No contact found for [Name] in the database.\""
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agentTool",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [
        1504,
        176
      ],
      "id": "68c2360d-553f-43fc-a239-1f2e7712442a",
      "name": "Contact Agent"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "toolDescription": "Call this tool to take action in email",
        "text": "={{ /*n8n-auto-generated-fromAI-override*/ $fromAI('Prompt__User_Message_', ``, 'string') }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=# Overview\nYou are an email assistant with access to Gmail. You will receive instructions that include a fully resolved email address — use that address exactly as provided.\n\n## Tools\n- **create Draft** — Create a Gmail draft or send an email. Use the exact email address passed to you.\n- **get Emails** — Retrieve emails. Always use this before creating a reply.\n- **Email Reply** — Reply to an existing email thread.\n\n## Rules\n- ALWAYS use the email address explicitly provided in your instructions. Do NOT look up or guess email addresses yourself.\n- If no email address is provided and only a name is given, respond: \"I need the email address for [Name] to proceed. Please provide it.\"\n- Write email body content in HTML format.\n- You cannot send emails directly — use the **create Draft** tool even when the user says \"send.\"\n\n## Final Reminder\nCurrent date/time: {{ $now.format('DD MMM YYYY, HH:mm') }}"
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agentTool",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [
        1888,
        176
      ],
      "id": "4d490b5a-83bf-4308-8d2d-6b663c234ae4",
      "name": "Email Agent"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "toolDescription": "Call this tool to take action in the calendar.",
        "text": "={{ /*n8n-auto-generated-fromAI-override*/ $fromAI('Prompt__User_Message_', ``, 'string') }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=### Overview\nYou are a calendar assistant with access to Google Calendar. You will receive instructions that include fully resolved email addresses for any attendees — use those addresses exactly as provided.\n\n### Tools\n1. **Get Events** — Retrieve calendar events. Always use this before updating or deleting.\n2. **Create Event** — Create an event with no attendees.\n3. **Create Event with Attendee** — Create an event with one or more attendees. Use the exact email address(es) passed to you.\n4. **Update Event** — Update an existing event. Fetch the event ID first using Get Events.\n5. **Delete Event** — Delete an event. Fetch the event ID first using Get Events.\n\n### Rules\n- ALWAYS use the attendee email address explicitly provided in your instructions. Do NOT look up, guess, or derive email addresses from names.\n- If no attendee email is provided but a name is mentioned, respond: \"I need the email address for [Name] to add them as an attendee. Please provide it.\"\n- Never assume the event ID — always call Get Events first when updating or deleting.\n\n### Final Reminder\nCurrent date/time: {{ $now.format('DD MMM YYYY, HH:mm') }}"
        }
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agentTool",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [
        2528,
        176
      ],
      "id": "a7556c8b-7c32-4e65-a806-3c45079bbf55",
      "name": "Calendar Agent"
    },
